<item>
            <title>[LU-14940] Source specified send to NID on different net should fail if there is no route</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14940</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using the lnetctl ping --source flag (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14939&quot; title=&quot;Allow specifying source NI for lnetctl ping&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14939&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14939&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) it is possible to send a ping from a local interface on @tcp1 to a remote interface on @tcp2 even though no route exists between these network types. This should not be allowed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
